parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electronic power steering system can cause the loss of power steering, making it difficult or impossible to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The power steering suddenly fails or becomes intermittent
the steering wheel becomes difficult or impossible to turn
the "service power steering" light appears on the dashboard
the steering wheel jerks or snaps back
the vehicle is difficult to control
especially when turning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling or shutting down can cause loss of control, accidents, or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle slows down and stalls
the check engine warning light illuminates
unknown warning lights flicker
smoke comes out of the vents
and the truck starts on fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the oil cooler can cause engine failure, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The truck leaks a large amount of oil
and the oil cooler gaskets degrade and fail.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The breaking of exhaust manifold bolts can cause exhaust gases to leak into the cabin, posing a health risk to passengers, and potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: A loud ticking noise comes from the engine
exhaust manifold bolts break
and exhaust gases leak into the cabin.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump can cause the engine to stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine stalls
and the high-pressure fuel pump fails.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine overheats
oil pressure drops
and the engine fails.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the plastic fan can cause damage to the transmission lines, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The plastic fan explodes
cutting through the transmission lines.
